5 compact, including, but not limited to:
6 1. Establishing the fiscal year of the Interstate Commission;
7 2. Establishing an executive committee, and such other
8 committees as may be necessary;
9 3. Providing for the establishment of committees and for
10 governing any general or specific delegation of authority or
11 function of the Interstate Commission;
12 4. Providing reasonable procedures for calling and conducting
13 meetings of the Interstate Commission, and ensuring reasonable
14 notice of each such meeting;
15 5. Establishing the titles and responsibilities of the
16 officers and staff of the Interstate Commission;
17 6. Providing a mechanism for concluding the operations of the
18 Interstate Commission and the return of surplus funds that may
19 exist upon the termination of the compact after the payment and
20 reserving of all of its debts and obligations.
21 7. Providing "start up" rules for initial administration of
22 the compact.
23 B. The Interstate Commission shall, by a majority of the
24 members, elect annually from among its members a chairperson, a
